free_txt: Orela
Two-section fission chamber, one containing
238U and the other containing 235U.
Orela
Resolution width Delta (eV) as a function of energy E
(eV): Delta**2 = aE + bE**2 + cE**3; a = 4kT/A, where
k Boltzmann constant, T absolute temperature, A
atomic number; b = 2/3 (lm**2 + ld**2))/(L**2), where
ld detector length, lm source moderator thickness,
L flight path length; c = 2/3 (d**2 +
(delta t)**2 + (delta tc)**2)/(mu**2 L**2), where d
pulse width, delta t channel width, delta tc time
resolution of electronic system, mu = 72.3 (eV)**0.5
micros/m. Numerical values for this experiment are
listed in the article.
Time-of-flight over 25 meter flight path.
